---
description: Use CSS custom properties defined in css/global.css for theme colors and fonts instead of hardcoded values
globs: css/**/*.css, agents/**/css/**/*.css
alwaysApply: false
---

- **Theme colors and fonts MUST be referenced via CSS custom properties**
  - Canonical variables live in [V:\css\global.css](mdc:css/global.css) under `:root`.
  - Bootstrap theming enhancements should reference the same variables (see [V:\css\bootstrap-overrides.css](mdc:css/bootstrap-overrides.css)).

- **Use variables for colors and fonts**

```css
.card {
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--deep-maroon) 0%, var(--dusk-brown-black) 100%);
  border: 2px solid var(--blood-red);
  font-family: var(--font-body);
  color: var(--text-mid);
}
```

- **New/edited CSS MUST NOT introduce near-duplicate hex values**
  - If a new theme color is required, it MUST be added to `:root` in `css/global.css` and used via `var(--...)`.
  - This keeps palette management centralized and consistent.

- **Bootstrap customization MUST remain scoped to Bootstrap classes**
  - See [Bootstrap.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/Bootstrap.mdc).
